translated: Leby, Martin Fritiof Tobias, clergyman, Mjölby, b. 1/2/98 in Hudiksvall. Married on the 25th with Carmen Tham. Children: Catharina b. 36, Henrik b. 30, Maria b. 40. - Studied: graduated high-school in 1919, graduated with a bachelor's degree in theology in 1920, completed theological candidate examination in 1923. Traveled to Denmark, Germany, Austria, and Italy. Assistant clergyman in Tranås, secretary in the Swedish Church Missionary Board in Uppsala, vicar in Kristberg in 1932, vicar in Mjölby since 1939. Part-time teacher at Mariannelund Practical School in 1919 and at Mjölby Secondary School from 1925 to 1928. Elected chairman of the church assembly, school council, and child welfare committee in Kristberg, chairman of the church council and school board, inspector for Mjölby Secondary School since 1940, and lecturer for the lecture association. Member of the child welfare committee, secretary in the Linköping Diocese Missionary Council, chairman of the Linköping Diocese Church Singing Association, member of the Swedish Flag's Day board, Mjölby Local Heritage Association, animal protection association, and Mjölby Scout Corps. Wrote: With a lit lantern (46)
